      "description": "There are many ways to tune in Forza, but this tuning app gives you results without a ton of information or time. Match your car to your driving style without fumbling through sliders and tutorials. This is the way.\n\nWhether you're building a Supra for the track, or the streets of Japan, you can get an expertly calculated base tune including gearing. Tune for the road, drifting, rally and more!\n\nYou can keep it stable if you're new to Forza, or put the car on edge if you are an expert driver. ForzaTune Pro updates the settings to match your preferences. \n\nYou also get an intelligent gearing calculator, the ability to save tunes, and finer control over your tune balance.\n\nHere are the complete specs if you'd like to learn more:\n\nONE APP TO TUNE THEM ALL\nForzaTune Pro has support for Forza Horizon 6 (Beta), Forza Motorsport (2023), Forza Horizon 5, Forza Horizon 4, Forza Motorsport 7 and also includes most vehicles in Forza Horizon 3 and Forza Motorsport 6.\n\nMAKE RACE, STREET, DRIFT, RALLY TUNES AND MORE\nThis tuning app gives you settings for many different situations. Create standard (road/track), drift, drag, rally/snow, and off-road tunes with ease.\n\nLEARN HOW TO QUICKLY FINE-TUNE\nAdjust the overall balance, turn entry balance, turn exit balance, ride stiffness, roll stiffness in seconds.\n\nRETUNE GEARS WITH EASE\nIncludes a gearing calculator option that lets you match race and drift transmission values to engine swaps or major power upgrades. \n\nTUNES ARE TAILORED TO EACH CAR\n1500+ vehicles covering Forza Horizon 6, FM '23, and games through Forza Motorsport 6. With free monthly updates for new cars and tracks!\n\nACCURATE FORMULAS\nForzaTune Pro builds a model of your car using your input plus its vehicle and track types. This model helps us make original, balanced tunes. Formulas are based on race engineering and adjusted for Forza. Results are also tested extensively with a gamepad and steering wheel/pedal set.\n\nSAVE AND MANAGE YOUR TUNES\nSave, edit, search and back up all of your tunes. Export and import options let you transfer your tunes to new devices or friends easily without logins or accounts.\n\n-----\nFAQs\n-----\nQ: Is this for beginners or experienced tuners?\nA: Both. Experienced tuners use it to save time and typically run higher oversteer settings. Newer tuners use it to learn how to tune and make sure the cars are stable after upgrading.\n\nQ: How do I use the app?\nA: Copy several car details from the game into ForzaTune, hit \"Calculate\" and copy the results into the tuning menu in Forza Motorsport or Forza Horizon. There is also a series of video tutorials on YouTube to get you started.\n\nQ: What settings and upgrades do I need?\nA: You will need racing upgrades like suspension, braking, anti-roll bars, and differential to change the values in the tuning menu. You can also use drift, rally and adjustable stock suspensions when available (like off-road buggies and some trucks in Horizon). You will also have the best results if you disable stability management (STM) and traction control (TCS) for lower class cars. Normal or simulation steering is fine.\n\nQ: Why is tuning your cars important?\nA: Upgrades can change how the car feels (for better or worse). ForzaTune lets you bring it back to a balanced setup. Also, tuning doesn't affect your PI or race restrictions—so this is how you can gain an advantage over other racers.\n\n---\nMake your own tunes, faster with ForzaTune Pro.",
